text: Now if only they would tell the true story of Heracles instead of glamorizing it. The true story of Heracles (not Hercules) is that he was a hotheaded guy who did not know his own strength and was the result of an incestuous double marriage affair. He was maliciously hated by his father's wife who sought to make his life miserable. For his punishment in accidentally killing his children (and inadvertently, his first wife), he was sent to serve his cousin until he completed ten nearly impossible tasks (it became twelve because the cousin said two of them didn't count).
